title: [Maelstrom Bay, Bottom]
description: The rocky wall curves from the south to the northwest.  Bladder rockweed clings to the stones and sways in slow motion.  Schools of mud shrimp scurry among the rockweed.  A few loggerhead sponges the size of large pumpkins grow in the sand of the bay floor.
paths: Obvious exits: south, southwest, west, northwest, up
